==Low German==

===Etymology===
{{root|nds|ine-pro|*gʷʰedʰ-}}
From {{inh|nds|osx|biddian}}, from {{inh|nds|gem-pro|*bidjaną||to ask}}, from {{der|nds|ine-pro|*gʷʰedʰ-}}. Compare {{cog|nl|bidden}}, {{cog|fy|bidde}}, {{cog|de|bitten}}, {{cog|en|bid}}, {{cog|da|bede}}.

===Verb===
{{head|nds|verb|third-person singular simple present|biddt|past tense|beed|past participle|beden|auxiliary verb|hebben}}

# to [[ask]]
#: ''He '''beed''' € 12,50 to kriegen.'' &mdash; He asked to have €12.50.
# to [[pray]]
#: ''De Sassen '''beden''' Saxnot mehr as alle annern Gödder.'' &mdash; The Saxons prayed Saxnot more than any other god.
# to [[request]]
#: ''Ik '''bidd''' en beten Stillde!'' &mdash; Silence!
# To [[bid]]
#: ''Ik '''bidd''' jo Fahrwoll.'' &mdash; I bid you farewell.

